Since $PRT$ is a straight line, $\angle PQR = 180^\circ - 40^\circ = 140^\circ$.  Since $QRS$ is a straight line, $\angle QRS = 180^\circ - x^\circ$.  Therefore, $\angle QRP = 180^\circ - 140^\circ - x^\circ = 40^\circ - x^\circ$.  Since $PRT$ is a straight line, $\angle PRS = 180^\circ - 40^\circ = 140^\circ$.  Therefore, $\angle QRS = 140^\circ - (40^\circ - x^\circ) = 100^\circ + x^\circ$.  Since $QRS$ is a straight line, $100^\circ + x^\circ = 180^\circ$, so $x = \boxed{80}$.  [asy]
