Let $n = \lfloor r \rfloor.$  Then $r = n + f,$ where $0 \le f < 1.$  Then
\[n + n + f = 15.5,\]so $2n + f = 15.5.$  Then $f = 15.5 - 2n.$

Since $0 \le f < 1,$
\[0 \le 15.5 - 2n < 1.\]Then $14.5 < 2n \le 15.5,$ so $7.25 < n \le 7.75.$  Since $n$ is an integer, $n$ can be 7 or 8.

If $n = 7,$ then $f = 15.5 - 2 \cdot 7 = 1.5.$  Then $r = 7 + 1.5 = 8.5.$

If $n = 8,$ then $f = 15.5 - 2 \cdot 8 = 0.5.$  Then $r = 8 + 0.5 = 8.5.$

Thus, there are $\boxed{2}$ values of $r.$

