There are $\binom{3}{2}=3$ ways to choose two teams out of three.  The probability that Team A is selected on a given day is $\frac{2}{3}$, so the probability that Team A is selected on at least two of the next three days is $\binom{3}{2}\left(\frac{2}{3}\right)^2\left(\frac{1}{3}\right)+\binom{3}{3}\left(\frac{2}{3}\right)^3=\boxed{\frac{20}{27}}$.  (Note that we must also consider the case where Team A is selected on all three days.) [asy]
