We have that $AB = 4$ and $AC = 5$, so by the Pythagorean Theorem, $BC = 3$.  Since $BC = 4 + 4$, we have $BD = 4$.  Since $BC = 5$, we have $CD = 3$.  Since $AB = 4$, we have $AD = 3$.  Since $AD = 3$ and $BD = 4$, we have $ABD$ is a $3-4-5$ right triangle, so $\angle ABD = 90^\circ$.  Since $\angle ABD = 90^\circ$ and $\angle BDA = 90^\circ$, we have $\angle BAD = 90^\circ$.  Therefore, $\triangle ABE$ is a $3-4-5$ right triangle, so its area is $\frac{1}{2} \cdot 3 \cdot 4 = \boxed{6}$. [asy]
pair pA, pB, pC, pD, pE;
pA = (0, 0);
pB = pA + 4 * dir(0);
pC = pA + 5 * dir(90);
pD = pB + 4 * dir(90);
pE = (4 * pA + 5 * pD) / 9;
draw(pA--pB--pC--pA);
draw(pA--pB--pD--pA);
label("$A$", pA, SW);
label("$B$", pB, SE);
label("$C$", pC, NW);
label("$D$", pD, NE);
label("$E$", pE, 2 * N);
label("$4$", pA--pB, S);
label("$5$", pA--pC, W);
label("$4$", pB--pD, E);
draw(rightanglemark(pB,pA,pC,8));
draw(rightanglemark(pD,pB,pA,8));
draw(pA--pE--pD);
label("$3$", pA--pE, NW);
label("$4$", pE--pD, NE);
label("$5$", pD--pB, NE);
[/asy]�始化

