Let $r$ be the radius of the circle.  Then the center of the circle is at $(r, r).$  Since the circle passes through $(p,0)$ and $(q,0),$ the distance from the center to these points is $r.$  Therefore,
\[(p - r)^2 + r^2 = (q - r)^2 + r^2.\]Expanding, we get
\[p^2 - 2pr + r^2 + r^2 = q^2 - 2qr + r^2 + r^2.\]Then $p^2 - q^2 = 2pr - 2qr,$ so
\[p - q = 2r.\]Then $q = p - 2r.$

